# Frontmatter Taxonomy — Schema, Heuristics, and Validation Rules

> **Source of truth** for `.md` frontmatter across this entire repository. The validator
> (`scripts/validate-frontmatter.mjs`), the index builder (`scripts/build-index.mjs`), the
> git hooks (`.husky/`), and CI (`.github/workflows/lint-frontmatter.yml`) all reference
> this file. Every agent, template, and skill must read this file — do **NOT** derive the
> schema from memory.
>
> Throughout this document, `{{TRACKER_KEY}}` is this project's ticket prefix (the
> identifier before the number, e.g. an issue id looks like `{{TRACKER_KEY}}-432`). If this
> project has no tracker (`{{TRACKER}} = none`), `ticket_id` is always `null` and the
> ticket-id grammar rule is relaxed accordingly.

---

## §1. Why frontmatter

Primary objective: prevent **authority errors** (the wrong artifact treated as the source of
truth when several versions of a fact coexist) and **blast-radius blindness** (a change to a
shared object whose dependents were never identified). Token reduction is a secondary benefit.

| Failure mode | Root cause | This schema addresses |
|---|---|---|
| **FM1** — Wrong artifact treated as SSOT | No formal `authority:` declaration when two artifacts state the same fact | `authority: ssot \| secondary \| superseded` encoded in frontmatter |
| **FM2** — Spec-vs-reality drift not caught | No systematic cross-check between an artifact and its dependents | `/audit-corpus` flags missing `authority:` and broken cross-references |
| **FM3** — Blast-radius blindness | No reverse lookup when a shared object changes | `affects:` field + `affects-lookup.mjs` reverse index |

---

## §2. Common fields (all `.md` files in scope)

```yaml
---
type: spec | report | review | council | doc | rule | agent | skill | archive | audit | handoff
title: "Human-readable short title"
ticket_id: {{TRACKER_KEY}}-432   # primary key when task-scoped; null for non-task docs
status: draft | active | in_progress | done | blocked | superseded | abandoned | living | snapshot | open | answered | decided | pending
authority: ssot | secondary | superseded   # see §4
affects: []                       # see §5; required for specs that touch shared objects
created: 2026-01-01               # ISO date
updated: 2026-01-01               # ISO date, bumped on every edit
tags: [auth, mfa]                 # lowercase kebab-case, max 8 entries
---
```

`ticket_id` is the universal task key. Its value follows this project's tracker
(`{{TRACKER}}`): a Linear/Jira id of the form `{{TRACKER_KEY}}-<number>`, or `null` for any
doc that is not task-scoped (and always `null` when `{{TRACKER}} = none`).

---

## §3. Per-type extensions

### `spec` — in `docs/claude_tasks/NN_*.md`

```yaml
task_number: 49                # integer; collisions resolved by appending 'b' to the newer file
domain: <free-form area>       # e.g. auth | ui | perf | data | infra | content | docs | tooling
phase: <project phase>         # e.g. pre-mvp | mvp | post-mvp (project-defined)
depends_on: [{{TRACKER_KEY}}-431, {{TRACKER_KEY}}-430]   # blocked-by relations
supersedes: {{TRACKER_KEY}}-300                           # optional
```

### `report` — in `docs/claude_tasks/reports/*` (DE Step-7 deliverable)

```yaml
task_number: 33
reviewer_findings: { critical: 0, high: 1, medium: 2, low: 3 }   # roll-up of the code-reviewer verdict
deployed: true | false
```

### `review` — in `docs/claude_tasks/reviews/*`

```yaml
reviewer: de | da | code-reviewer | devils-advocate
task_number: 33
verdict: <see per-reviewer enum below>
critical_count: 0
high_count: 2
```

**Per-reviewer `verdict:` enum (the validator enforces it per the `reviewer:` field):**

| Reviewer | Norse alias (cross-ref) | Allowed verdicts |
|---|---|---|
| `de` | — | `approve` \| `approve_with_fixes` \| `reject_needs_rework` |
| `da` | — | `approve` \| `approve_with_fixes` \| `reject_needs_rework` |
| `code-reviewer` | (formerly heimdall) | `safe` \| `non_blocking` \| `not_safe_to_deploy` |
| `devils-advocate` | (formerly loki) | `mostly_grounded_dissent` \| `mostly_speculative` |

> The code-reviewer verdict mirrors the deploy gate: **any CRITICAL finding ⇒ `not_safe_to_deploy`**.
> The devils-advocate never approves — its verdict only characterizes how grounded the
> objections were (Grounded-Dissent Protocol).

### `council` — in `docs/claude_tasks/council/*`

```yaml
topic: <one-line decision topic>
decision_id: 78                # links to a strategy.md decision-log entry
participants: [pm, de, da, code-reviewer, devils-advocate]   # devils-advocate is mandatory
```

### `doc` — in `docs/*.md` (excluding the sub-types above)

```yaml
last_reviewed: 2026-01-01
owner: <name or role>
related_decisions: [76, 78]    # optional — strategy.md decision-log entries
```

### `handoff` — in `docs/claude_tasks/*` (multi-session task handoff)

```yaml
task_number: 49
ticket_id: {{TRACKER_KEY}}-403
next_action: "<the single next step for the resuming session>"
```

> A `handoff` is the artifact a *transitory close* writes when a task spans more than one
> session (see the lifecycle). It is the durable form of `context_snapshot.md` for one task.

### `agent`, `skill`, `rule` — in `agents/`, `skills/`, `.claude/rules/**/*.md`

These files carry their own native frontmatter. Preserve existing `name:`, `description:`,
`tools:`, `model:`, `allowed-tools:` fields. You MAY add `tags:` if it does not conflict. Do
**NOT** add `ticket_id:` — these files are not task-scoped.

### `archive` — in `docs/claude_tasks/archive/*` and `docs/**/archive/*`

```yaml
archived_date: 2026-01-01
superseded_by: docs/strategy.md   # path or ticket_id of the replacement
original_date: 2026-01-01
```

### `audit` — in `docs/audits/*`

```yaml
audit_period: 2026-W19           # ISO week, or a date range
issues: { high: 0, medium: 3, low: 7 }
```

