## §4. `authority:` semantics

| Value | Meaning | Wins when |
|---|---|---|
| `ssot` | Source of truth. If two artifacts disagree, this one wins. | Always — at most **one** `ssot` per `(ticket_id, surface)` pair. |
| `secondary` | Reference / context, not authoritative. | Loses to `ssot` on any conflict (reports, reviews, handoffs). |
| `superseded` | Historical, no longer authoritative. | Never wins. Read-only audit trail. |

**Override rule:** an explicit `authority:` declaration in frontmatter always wins over the
path-derived default in §5.

---

## §5. Path-derived `authority:` and `type:` defaults

A backfill heuristic derives these from the file path when an author has not declared them.
An explicit frontmatter declaration always wins.

| Path glob | Default `authority:` | Default `type:` |
|---|---|---|
| `docs/claude_tasks/NN_*.md` | `secondary` | `spec` |
| `docs/claude_tasks/alpha_tests/*` | `ssot` | `spec` |
| `docs/claude_tasks/reports/*` | `secondary` | `report` |
| `docs/claude_tasks/reviews/*` | `secondary` | `review` |
| `docs/claude_tasks/council/*` | `ssot` | `council` |
| `docs/claude_tasks/archive/*` | `superseded` | `archive` |
| `docs/strategy.md` | `ssot` | `doc` |
| `docs/architecture.md` | `ssot` | `doc` |
| `docs/project_chronicle.md` | `ssot` | `doc` |
| `docs/knowledge_base/*.md` | `ssot` | `doc` |
| `docs/audits/*` | `secondary` | `audit` |
| `docs/**/archive/*` | `superseded` | `archive` |
| `agents/*.md` | `ssot` | `agent` |
| `skills/**/*.md` | `ssot` | `skill` |
| `.claude/rules/**/*.md` | `ssot` | `rule` |

Fallback for any unmatched path: `type: doc`, `authority: secondary`.

> The frozen acceptance tests under `docs/claude_tasks/alpha_tests/` are `ssot`: once sealed
> they are the binding pass/fail contract. `/audit-corpus` flags a sealed alpha test that was
> modified after sealing as a **High** finding (the FREEZE RULE).

