## §6. `affects:` semantics

Free-form list of canonical object identifiers naming what a change touches, so a reverse
lookup (`scripts/affects-lookup.mjs`) can answer "what depends on this object?". Required on
`type: spec` whenever any commit on the spec's branch changes a **shared object** (a schema,
a public API/route, a data contract, an environment variable, a scheduled job, or a shared
repo surface). Purely local changes MAY omit `affects:`.

### Allowed prefixes (stack-neutral)

| Prefix | Meaning | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `data.<object>` | A persisted data object (table, collection, dataset, model) | `data.users`, `data.invoices` |
| `fn.<name>()` | A stored/shared function or procedure | `fn.compute_balance()`, `fn.is_owner()` |
| `api.<path>` | A public API endpoint or route | `api./users/:id`, `api./auth/login` |
| `ui.<surface>` | A user-facing page/view/component | `ui.dashboard`, `ui.components/DatePicker` |
| `auth.<surface>` | An authentication/authorization surface | `auth.session`, `auth.mfa` |
| `job.<workflow>` | A scheduled/background job or pipeline stage | `job.nightly-sync`, `job.fx-rates` |
| `env.<var>` | An environment variable / secret name | `env.DATABASE_URL`, `env.API_TOKEN` |
| `migration.<id>` | A database migration / schema-change unit | `migration.0042` |
| `dep.<package>` | An external dependency | `dep.express`, `dep.pydantic` |
| `repo.<section>` | A repository-level surface | `repo.docs`, `repo.scripts`, `repo.ci`, `repo.hooks`, `repo.layout` |

This prefix set is the generic baseline. A project MAY extend it with stack-specific prefixes
by documenting the addition here (this file is the SSOT, so the addition is then valid); the
validator checks `affects:` items against the grammar declared in this section.

